description.en-US: Curated collection of high-quality Android applications. Features official binaries from trusted developers, including privacy tools, communication apps, open-source alternatives, and useful utilities. Covers both FOSS and proprietary applications for enhanced mobile experience.

summary.en-US: A V2Ray client for Android, support Xray core and v2fly core

description.en-US: A V2Ray client for Android, support Xray core and v2fly core Features - Support for multiple protocols: V2Ray, Xray, Shadowsocks, Trojan, VMess, VLESS - Advanced routing with geoip and geosite data - Subscription support for automatic server updates - Built-in speed test and latency measurement - QR code scanning for easy server configuration - Import/export configuration files - Multiple proxy modes and routing rules - Support for XTLS encryption - Custom DNS settings - Statistics and traffic monitoring - Dark and light themes

summary.en-US: A FOSS Android client for WireGuard and AmneziaWG with auto-tunneling.

description.en-US: An alternative VPN client app for WireGuard with additional features Features - Add tunnels via .conf file, zip, manual entry, or QR code - Auto connect to VPN based on Wi-Fi SSID, ethernet, or mobile data - Split tunneling by application with search - WireGuard support for kernel and userspace modes - Always-On VPN support - Export tunnels to zip - Quick tile support for VPN toggling - Static shortcuts support for primary tunnel for automation integration - Intent automation support for all tunnels - Automatic service restart after reboot - Battery preservation measures

summary.en-US: NekoBox for Android / sing-box / universal proxy toolchain for Android

description.en-US: Universal proxy toolchain for Android powered by sing-box core with support for multiple protocols[1] Features - Support for multiple proxy protocols: SOCKS (4/4a/5), HTTP(S), SSH, Shadowsocks, VMess, Trojan, VLESS, AnyTLS, ShadowTLS, TUIC, Hysteria 1/2, WireGuard[1] - Plugin support for extended protocols (Trojan-Go, NaïveProxy, Mieru)[1] - Multiple subscription format support (Shadowsocks, ClashMeta, v2rayN, sing-box outbound)[1] - Intuitive Android interface based on shadowsocks-android and SagerNet[1] - Built-in web dashboard powered by Yacd-meta[1] - Powered by robust sing-box core technology[1] Important Note NekoBox does not provide VPN services. Users are responsible for acquiring or setting up their own servers. Please comply with applicable laws in your jurisdiction when utilizing the app. Warning Google Play version has been controlled by third party since May 2024 and is non-open source[1]. Use only official GitHub releases.

summary.en-US: A proxy management app powered by Xray core with support for multiple protocols.

description.en-US: Happ is a mobile application designed for convenient proxy server management, powered by the robust Xray core. The app features an intuitive interface and a range of useful functions, making it an essential tool for managing connections. Features - Configuration of proxy servers based on flexible routing rules - Support for multiple modern protocols including VLESS (Reality), VMess, Trojan, Shadowsocks, Socks - Private by design - no data collection, information stays on your device - Flexible routing rules for advanced proxy management - Intuitive interface for easy connection management - Powered by robust Xray core technology Important Note Happ does not provide VPN services for purchase. Users are responsible for acquiring or setting up their own servers. Please comply with applicable laws in your jurisdiction when utilizing the app.
